------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party interoperability and optional dependencies
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

scorewright's core ships no third-party runtime dependencies. The components
below are referenced only by optional integrations (extras), examples, and
benchmarks. scorewright does not vendor their source; it interoperates with
their public interfaces. Each remains under its own license, held by its
respective authors.

* OpenEvolve — Apache License 2.0.
  Target of the `scorewright.adapters.openevolve` adapter (the adapter emits a
  callable matching OpenEvolve's evaluator contract). Installed via the
  `openevolve` extra to run the example/benchmark.
  https://github.com/codelion/openevolve

* microsandbox — Apache License 2.0.
  Optional VM-isolated sandbox backend (interface stub in v0.1.0a1).
  Installed via the `microsandbox` extra.
  https://github.com/microsandbox/microsandbox

The following projects informed scorewright's design and are candidate
interop targets for later versions; they are not dependencies of v0.1.0a1:

* PrimeIntellect "verifiers" — MIT License (planned adapter, v0.2).
* SWE-ReX — MIT License.
* Inspect AI — MIT License.

